body:
Hi @ijuma we're looking at it, but can't find a test that exercises the ticket refresh. 
We will try a manual test, by setting a low refresh time, and look at the logs to see if they appear OK.

BTW, even if a refresh causes a `reLogin()` to fail, in `KerberosLogin` the method
```
    @Override
    public Subject subject() {
        return subject;
    }
```
is returning the same subject instance obtained by the initial call to `login()`
and not the updated subject from the new `LoginContext` created by `reLogin()`

is this intentional ?

@edoardocomar, yes, we are unfortunately lacking automated tests for that. It's what's blocking this PR of mine: https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/1522. For this PR, a manual check would be OK.

Regarding the subject, in `reLogin`, we pass the subject to `LoginContext`, so that seems OK.

Finally, seems like there are conflicts in this branch. Would you mind rebasing? I'll try to review it (and possibly merge it) today.
